content.description: Start to the right of Fireside Chat on the most overhanging portion of the wall. Sit start on a big rail with a wide left foot. Move up and right to the sharp but awesome flake sticking out of the wall. Continue up and left to smaller but good pockets to the awkward top out.

Named this because of the fire pit that is directly below this route, this is the first route you should see as you cross the creek. Sit start with hands in good pockets. Work up through smaller pockets and get your feet up. Switch your left upside down and use the starting pocket as an undercling. Make the reachy move to the next good pocket and work up and right to the slopey and often times dirty top out.

Called the warm up wall because it is the first rock you see as you cross the creek coming from the main parking area. Basically a short cliff-line that has a couple of solid problems on in that will surely have a dirty top out waiting for you.
